<DOC><DOCNO> AP880516-0135 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-16-88 1528EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-US-PLO     05-16 0140</FIRST><SECOND>AM-US-PLO,140</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Rejects Arafat Claim on Abu Jihad Killing</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The State Department on Monday rejected in``the strongest possible terms'' an alleged statement by PalestineLiberation Organization chairman Yasser Arafat that the UnitedStates participated in the assassination of the PLO's secondranking official, Abu Jihad.   ``Such irresponsible statements can only encourage further actsof violence and terrorism,'' said department spokesman CharlesRedman.   Redman said Arafat made the allegation in an interview on May 11.   ``Arafat should disavow these dangerous and false allegationsimmediately,'' Redman said.   According to Redman, Arafat is reported to have said, ``TheUnited States also participated in the assassination of Abu Jihad.''   The PLO leader was gunned down in Tunis on April 16. Publishedreports have attributed the killing to an Israeli commando squad.Israel has refused comment on the allegation.</TEXT></DOC>